results.title: Avengers (1963) #303
results.description: Quasar impresses Captain America after he saves Hawkeye in battle with Super-Nova. The East and West Coast Avengers agree to regroup as one team. Mr. Fantastic convinces Super-Nova to take his rage elsewhere, and search for Nebula in the timestream. Captain America makes a formal bid for Quasar to join the team.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #304
results.description: The Avengers encounter Puma, a genetically engineered Native American who is tracking a mutant from his own tribe. The young mutant in question, Charles Little Sky, accidentally opens a dimensional rift which frees the U-Foes from exile.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #305
results.description: The Avengers Hydrobase gets attacked by a horde of lava men! Will the Avengers be able to stop the infiltration when the odds are stacked against them?

results.title: Avengers (1963) #306
results.description: The origin of the lava men revealed! The Avengers are trapped inside a lava ball by Jinku, the lava mens’ witch doctor. Will Sub Mariner be able to bail his teammates out of this bind?

results.title: There Is a Fire Down Below
Avengers (1963) #307
results.description: The Avengers continue to battle Jinku in a red-hot lava fight. Invisible Woman attempts to save the Hyrdobase from a lava column. Plus, a hero takes a near fatal blow!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #308
results.description: No longer under Jinku’s control, the reformed Lava Men help the Avengers get Gilgamesh to safety. Gilgamesh is beyond the aid of mortal medicine, and the team must turn to the Eternal Sersi to save their fallen teammate.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #309
results.description: Olympia, realm of the gods, sucked into the Negative Zone! Guest-starring the always quirky Great Lakes Avengers!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #310
results.description: The Avengers take on Blastaar, ruler of the Negative Zone! Plus, the return of the Eternals!

results.title: Has the Whole World Gone Mad?!?
The Crossing Line:  Part One:  The Waterwind Interdiction
Avengers (1963) #321
results.description: The Avengers, surrounded by non-powered allies, must capture a nuclear submarine before terrorists attack the shores of Newfoundland.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #322
results.description: The return of the Atalanteans! While trying to prevent nuclear war on the shores of Newfoundland, the Avengers encounter more trouble in an unprovoked attack from Atlantis!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #323
results.description: Shaman of Alpha Flight saves the day when he contains a nuclear explosion in his mystical medicine pouch. The only problem? The Avengers are now trapped in the dimensional pockets of the pouch, alongside heavy doses of radiation and the madmen who planted the bomb!

results.title: One World's Not Enough For All of Us
Avengers (1963) #324
results.description: The Avengers must work with Atalanteans and members of the Peace Corpse to escape Shaman’s medicine pouch before it’s too late! Will the Avengers, their allies, and their enemies, remain in a dimensional pocket for all time?

results.title: Avengers (1963) #325
results.description: The Machinesmith, Minister Blood, and Mother Night crash Sersi’s party at Avengers Mansion. Will the team be able to keep themselves, and their partygoers, out of harm’s way?

results.title: Avengers (1963) #326
results.description: The Avengers finish up modifications on their new Avengers Complex. But when two uninvited guests crash the front gate, will the team re-consider a new security system? Featuring Rage and the irradiated anti-hero, Ramskov!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #327
results.description: The Avengers continue to fend off radiation attacks from Ramskov. Running out of options, the team decides to transport their new foe to an alternate dimension where magic reigns supreme.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #328
results.description: After an attack from the Unspeakable One, the Avengers plan a retreat to their home dimension with Ramskov in tow. Plus, the origin of Rage revealed!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #329
results.description: Avengers of the past and present re-convene to decide on a new team roster. Plus, Cap makes an announcement that will leave readers reeling!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #330
results.description: Trapped in exile, and separated from each other, the Avengers must stand alone against the Tetrarchs of Entropy. Back on earth, the Unspeakable One aligns himself with local hoodlums and takes Rage’s grandmother hostage!

results.title: For Here We Make Our Stand
Avengers (1963) #341
results.description: After a racial hate crime, Rage goes on record and makes a few public comments that make Captain America squirm. Adding to the controversy? The Sons of the Serpent demand blood from Rage and the New Warriors!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #342
results.description: The Sons of the Serpent attack the New Warriors, and the Avengers make it their top priority to uncover their base of operation. Who is the Hate Monger? And why is he perpetuating violence against the team? Plus, a disgraced Avenger is given less-than-two-weeks-notice by Captain America!
